<DOC><DOCNO> AP891012-0177 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-12-89 2056EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-RailFines     10-12 0083</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Rail Fines,80</SECOND><HEAD>Government Collects $4.46 Million In Fines From Railroads</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Railroads paid the government $4.46 million infines for safety violation during the past year, the FederalRailroad Administration said Thursday.   The fines cover problems with track, locomotives, freight cars,signals and operating practices, said rail Administrator Gilbert E.Carmichael.   He said the agency uses civil penalties to focus attention onproblems that pose a threat to rail safety. The fines cover fiscal1989 which ended Sept. 30.</TEXT></DOC>